'''Tir Asleen''' was considered the greatest of all kingdoms on the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] of [[Andowyne]].<ref name="Databank" />

In the beautiful and inspiring [[Castle/Legends|castles]] that dotted the kingdom's highest hills, rulers maintained control for nearly a thousand by interacting with [[The Force/Legends|the Force]] and creating an environment in which the natives wanted to live in peace and harmony. Other buildings housed immense [[Library/Legends|libraries]], where sorcerers and philosophers studied side-by-side. The peace came to an end when [[Bavmorda]] rose to power by tapping into the [[Dark side of the Force/Legends|dark side of the Force]]. In her conquests, Bavmorda froze Tir Alseen in stasis, sealing it off from outsiders and forcing its inhabitants into a state of [[Suspended animation/Legends|suspended animation]].<ref name="Databank" />

When [[Thorn Drumheller|Willow Ufgood]] and [[Fin Raziel]] defeated Bavmorda, Tir Asleen was freed from its captivity, and its people were once again allowed to roam its streets. Shortly afterward, however, Tir Asleen was razed during the Cataclysm. Nothing was left standing in its place, and the entire population of the kingdom disappeared.<ref name="Databank" />

{{Loc-stub}}

==Behind the scenes==
On [[April 1]], [[2006]], [[StarWars.com]] updated its [[Databank (original)|Databank]] with elements from the film and its spin-off novels, indicating that [[Willow (film)|''Willow'']] would be added to the ''[[Star Wars]]'' continuity. Elaborate databank entries were written which attempted to plausibly fit the film into the history of the ''[[Star Wars]]'' universe. However, two days later, it was revealed to be an [[Wikipedia:April Fools' Day|April Fools' joke]], and thus non-[[canon]].<ref name="DB-The Shadow War Chronicles">{{DB|updates|401/news20060401.html|The Shadow War Chronicles}} {{C|[https://web.archive.org/web/20080325023230/www.starwars.com/databank/updates/401/news20060401.html backup link] on [[Wikipedia:Internet Archive|Archive.org]]}}</ref>

